result.execSummary:
The defendant Krista L Baxter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 9:50 am [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Robert Mawdsley presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Krista L Baxter in court with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Hall submits AMENDED information; Service of amended information admitted; reading waived

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1 & #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Counts #1 & #2, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
--Comply with all existing juvenile court orders regarding M.L. and A.L.
--Not engage in any physical discipline of any child
--To undergo any other type of assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program, per Agent
--No acts/threats of violence
--To pay statutory costs of $486 ($243 each count)
--To pay $400 DNA Surcharge ($200 each count)
--No contact with M.L. or A.L., unless authorized by DOC and any existing juvenile court orders

Days credit for time already served: 1 day
Recess: 10:10 am

Case called at 1:24pm [mo]
Defendant Krista L Baxter in court with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek.  DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.


As to the State's Motion to Admit Forensic Interview: 
--Atty. Svehlek opposes the motion; gives arguments
--arguments given by DA Happ
--The Court continues this Motion hearing to allow time to review the Jimmie R.R. case (232 Wis 2d 138, 606 N.W. 2d 196)  and determine whether the interviewer properly addressed possible punishments for lying.


As to the State's Motion to Admit Other Acts of Evidence:
--The Court grants the State's Motion to Admit Other Acts of Evidence; gives basis
--The Court requires the State to submit cautionary instruction due by FSSC date

As to the State's Motion in Limine
--Atty. Svehlek questions the Court 

As to State's Motion to Admit Statements:
--No Miranda/ Goodchild hearing needed, as both parties agree that these rights were not violated
